<div class="essay-head">
  <h1>About</h1>
</div>
<article>
  <figure class="about-photo">{% img "src/assets/photo/artur-portret.jpg", "Artur Paprocki — portrait, shirt with jacket over the shoulder", [248, 496] %}</figure>
  <p>I'm the founder and CEO of Veles Productions — a Warsaw studio that has been combining creative production with building AI agents since 2022. We started in virtual production: LED walls, motion capture, real-time rendering in Unreal Engine. Today that same workshop is meeting robotics and AI agents — the direction Veles is pushing hardest in 2026. For our clients — in film, television, defence, medicine, entertainment, and gaming — we help build worlds that until recently would have required teams ten times the size.</p>
  <p>I don't consider myself a programmer or a technology theorist. I'm a practitioner — I learn what I write about by building it with my team, often through trial and error. My strengths are unconventional thinking, early adoption of new tools, and passing on what I've learned.</p>
  <p>I write this blog because writing forces me to think more precisely than conversation does. What interests me is the intersection of creativity and technology — not as a topic to comment on from the sidelines, but as the place where I run a company every day. A new essay appears here every two weeks, in Polish and in English.</p>
  <p>The easiest way to find me is on <a href="{{ site.links.linkedin }}">LinkedIn</a>. You can also write to <a href="mailto:{{ site.links.email }}">{{ site.links.email }}</a>.</p>
</article>
